<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="next-adj">next <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nekst/    美 /nekst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 下一个的；接下来的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Drop me at the next corner, please. 
请让我在下一个拐角处下车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Next time</strong> I go skiing, I’ll wear warmer clothes. 
下次去滑雪的时候，我要穿得更暖和一些。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The next thing you need to decide is what you are going to paint, a portrait, a landscape or a still life.
接下来你要决定的是画什么——是一幅肖像画，一幅风景画，还是一幅静物画。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 3</footer></div>

<p>注: 在时间上，指以现在为基准的“下一个”时，不加the。指以过去或未来某时间为基准的“下一个”时，加the。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m going on vacation <strong>next week / month</strong>. 
下周/下月，我要去度假。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was sick during the night but felt better <strong>the next day</strong>.
我那天晚上生病了，不过第二天感觉好些了。</p></div></div>